## 📝 3. Convenciones de Nomenclatura

### Variables y Funciones

```typescript
✅ CORRECTO: camelCase descriptivo
const productList = [];
const isLoading = false;
const hasError = true;
const userCount = 10;

function calculateTotal() {}
function handleSubmit() {}
function fetchUserData() {}

❌ INCORRECTO:
const ProductList = [];
const loading = false; // Prefiere isLoading
const error = true; // Prefiere hasError
const num = 10; // No descriptivo

function calc() {} // Abreviado
function submit() {} // Sin contexto
function get() {} // Demasiado genérico
```

### Booleanos

```typescript
✅ CORRECTO: Usa prefijos is, has, should, can
const isVisible = true;
const hasAccess = false;
const shouldUpdate = true;
const canEdit = false;

❌ INCORRECTO:
const visible = true;
const access = false;
const update = true;
```

### Constantes Globales

```typescript
✅ CORRECTO: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
const API_BASE_URL = 'https://api.example.com';
const MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS = 3;
const DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE = 20;

❌ INCORRECTO:
const apiBaseUrl = 'https://api.example.com';
const maxRetryAttempts = 3;
```

### Eventos y Handlers

```typescript
✅ CORRECTO: Prefijo handle/on
// En el componente padre
const handlePress = () => {};
const handleSubmit = () => {};
const handleInputChange = () => {};

// En el componente hijo (prop)
<Button onPress={handlePress} />
<Input onChange={handleInputChange} />

❌ INCORRECTO:
const press = () => {};
const submit = () => {};
const clickHandler = () => {}; // Usa "Press" en móvil, no "Click"
```

