## 🚫 13. Anti-Patrones a Evitar

```typescript
❌ 1. Modificar state directamente
products.push(newProduct); // ¡NO!
setProducts(products);

✅ Usa spread/inmutabilidad
setProducts([...products, newProduct]);

❌ 2. Demasiados useState
const [name, setName] = useState('');
const [email, setEmail] = useState('');
const [phone, setPhone] = useState('');
// ... 10 más

✅ Agrupa en un objeto o usa useReducer
const [form, setForm] = useState({
  name: '',
  email: '',
  phone: '',
});

❌ 3. Lógica en el JSX
<View>
  {products.filter(p => p.active).map((p, i) => (
    <Text key={i}>{p.name}</Text>
  ))}
</View>

✅ Extrae a variables
const activeProducts = products.filter(p => p.active);
return (
  <View>
    {activeProducts.map((product) => (
      <Text key={product.id}>{product.name}</Text>
    ))}
  </View>
);

❌ 4. Keys con índices
{items.map((item, index) => <Item key={index} />)}

✅ Usa IDs únicos
{items.map((item) => <Item key={item.id} />)}
```

